{"title_page": "1999 Super League Grand Final", "text_new": "{{Infobox rugby league football match\n|year         = 1999\n|title        = Super League Grand Final\n|image        = \n|imagesize    = \n|alt          = 1999 Super League logo\n|home         = [[Bradford Bulls]]\n|away         = [[St Helens R.F.C.|St. Helens]]\n|home_abbr    = BRA {{leagueicon|Bradford|16}}\n|away_abbr    = ST H {{leagueicon|St Helens|16}}\n|home_half1   = 6\n|home_half2   = 0\n|home_total   = 6\n|away_half1   = 2\n|away_half2   = 6\n|away_total   = 8\n|date         = 9 October 1999\n|stadium      = [[Old Trafford (football ground)|Old Trafford]]\n|location     = {{flagicon|ENG}} Manchester\n|MoM_title    = [[Harry Sunderland Trophy]]\n|MoM          = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Henry Paul]] ({{leagueicon|Bradford|16}} [[Bradford Bulls|Bradford]])\n|anthem_title = [[And did those feet in ancient time|Jerusalem]]\n|anthem       = \n|referee      = [[Stuart Cummings]]\n|attendance   = 50,717\n|network      = [[Sky Sports]]\n|commentators = [[Eddie Hemmings (rugby league)|Eddie Hemmings]]\n|commentators2= [[Mike Stephenson]]\n|commentators3= \n|tournaments  = [[Super League Grand Final]]\n|last         = [[1998 Super League Grand Final|1998]]\n|next         = [[2000 Super League Grand Final|2000]]\n}}\nThe '''1999 Super League Grand Final''' was the conclusive and championship-deciding game of the [[Super League IV]] season. The match was played between English clubs [[St Helens R.F.C.|St. Helens]] and [[Bradford Bulls]] on Saturday 9 October 1999, at [[Old Trafford (football ground)|Old Trafford]], Manchester, UK.\n\n==Background==\n{{further|Super League IV}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Position\"|\n!width=175 |Team\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Played\"|Pld\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Won\"|W\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Drawn\"|D\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Lost\"|L\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Points for\"|PF\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Points against\"|PA\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Points difference\"|PD\n! style=\"width:20px;\" abbr=\"Points\"|Pts\n|- \n|1||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Image:Bullscolours.svg|16x16px]] [[Bradford Bulls]]\n|30||25||1||4||897||445||+452||'''51'''\n|- \n|2||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Image:Saintscolours.svg|16x16px]] [[St Helens R.F.C.|St. Helens]]\n|30||23||0||7||1034||561||+473||'''46'''\n|}\n\n===Route to the Final===\n====Bradford Bulls====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;margin-left:1em;float:right\"\n<!-- |+ '''Leeds''' -->\n!width=\"25\" | Round\n!width=\"150\" | Opposition\n!width=\"60\" | Score\n|-\n!scope=row style=\"text-align:center\"| Qualifying Semi-Final\n| {{leagueicon|st helens|16}} [[St Helens RFC|St Helens]] (H)\n|bgcolor=DDFFDD| 40-4\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color:white;\"| <small>'''Key:''' (H) = Home venue; (A) = Away venue; (N) = [[Home advantage#Neutral venues|Neutral venue]].</small>\n|}\n\n====St Helens====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;margin-left:1em;float:right\"\n<!-- |+ '''Leeds''' -->\n!width=\"25\" | Round\n!width=\"150\" | Opposition\n!width=\"60\" | Score\n|-\n!scope=row style=\"text-align:center\"| Qualifying Play-Off\n| {{leagueicon|leeds|16}} [[Leeds Rhinos]] (H)\n| bgcolor=DDFFDD|38-14\n|-\n!scope=row style=\"text-align:center\"| Qualifying Semi-Final\n| {{leagueicon|bradford|16}} [[Bradford Bulls]] (A)\n|bgcolor=FFDDDD| 40-4\n|-\n!scope=row style=\"text-align:center\"| Final Eliminator\n| {{leagueicon|castleford|16}} [[Castleford Tigers]] (H)\n| bgcolor=DDFFDD|36-6\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color:white;\"| <small>'''Key:''' (H) = Home venue; (A) = Away venue; (N) = [[Home advantage#Neutral venues|Neutral venue]].</small>\n|}\n\n==Match details==\n\n{{rugbyleaguebox |\nbg = #eeeeee |\ndate = 9 October 1999<!--<br /> 18:00 [[Western European Summer Time|UTC+1]] Need to verify this--> |\nteam1 = [[Brad