{"title_page": "Ivan Daniels", "text_new": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n|name = Ivan Daniels\n|image = \n|caption = \n|league  = \n|team    = \n|position = [center (basketball)Forward]\n|birth_date = February 8th 1963\n|birth_place = Chicago IL, Cook County Hospital.\n|nationality = American & Argentine\n|height_ft = 6  \n|height_in = 10\n|weight_lb = 235\n|number = Grade School #1/High School #53/20/& 41. University #41. Semi Pro Numbers- 9/5/& 15.\n \n|high_school =  Lake Park H.S. Roselle IL.\n|college = [[UIC Flames The University of Illinois at Chicago]] (1981\u20131985)\n| draft_year      = 1985\n| draft_round     = 5\n| draft_pick      = 111\n| draft_team      = [[Indiana Pacers]]\n| draft_league    = NBA\n|career_start = \n|career_end = \n|career_number = \n|years1 = 1985 |team1 = Tonego '65 (basketball) Haaksbergen,Holland\n|years2 = 1986 |team2 = Club Independiente de Z\u00e1rate (basketball) Z\u00e1rate, Argentina\n|years3 = 1987 |team3 = [[Newcastle Falcons (basketball)|Newcastle Falcons]] Newcastle Australia\n|highlights = Captain of the Lancers Frosoph Boys basketball team 1979-80 Leading scorer and rebounder. Second team all conference Upstate 8 1980. Confrences Leading rebounder. MVP Lake Park Thanksgiving Invitational Tournament 1980. All Tournament team at the Luthor North Christmas Tournament 1980. Team Captian Lancers Varsity Boys Basketball Team 1980-81. 1st team All Conference in the Upstate 8, 1981. Inducted into the Lake Park H.S. Athletic Hall of Fame for Basketball. Lake Park High School's all time leading rebounder.\n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Ivan Daniels''' is an American former semi professional [[basketball]] player. He was 6'10&nbsp;ft, 235&nbsp;lbs<ref>{{cite news|title=Sewell Signs Pact With Broncos|url=http://newsok.com/article/2115632|accessdate=31 March 2018|work=[[The Oklahoman]]|date=22 July 1985}}</ref> and played the [[Center (basketball)|center]] position.<ref name=\"orlando-sentinel-1985\">{{cite news|title=Basketball|url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1985-07-22/sports/0310400152_1_detroit-lions-15-day-disabled-list-nose-tackle|accessdate=31 March 2018|work=[[Orlando Sentinel]]|date=22 July 1985}}</ref>\n\n==College==\nDaniels played four seasons of [[college basketball]] for [[University of Illinois at Chicago]]. He was a key member of the 1983-84 [[UIC Flames|UIC]] team that won the [[Summit League|Association of Mid-Continent Universities Conference]] regular season title and set a then-school record with 22 victories. During his senior year, Daniels averaged 17.7 points per game.<ref>{{cite web|title=UIC Hall of Fame|url=http://uicflames.com/sports/2016/6/14/hof-mbb-html.aspx?id=116|website=uicflames.com|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Playing career==\nAfter his college career, Daniels was drafted by the [[Indiana Pacers]] in the 5th round of the [[1985 NBA Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|title=1985 NBA Draft|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/draft/NBA_1985.html|accessdate=31 March 2018|work=basketball-reference.com}}</ref> He was cut by the Pacers before the start of the season<ref name=\"orlando-sentinel-1985\"/> and went on to play professionally with, among others, Tonego '65 in the [[Dutch Basketball League]] during the 1985\u20131986 season<ref>{{cite web|title=Spelers Dossier|url=http://db.basketball.nl/db/overzicht/spelersdossier.pl?detail=Dossier&spl_ID=9392|website=db.basketball.nl|accessdate=31 March 2018|language=Dutch}}</ref> and the [[Newcastle Falcons (basketball)|Newcastle Falcons]] of the Australian [[National Basketball League (Australia)|National Basketball League]] during the [[1987 NBL season]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Player Profile - Ivan Daniels|url=http://websites.sportstg.com/team_info.cgi?player=Ivan%20Daniels&action=PSTATS&player_id=190395414&client=0-189-12323-125718-369918|website=sportstg.com|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.sports-reference.com/cbb/players/ivan-daniels-1.html College statistics] at [https://www.sports-reference.com sports-reference.com]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniels, Ivan}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indiana Pacers players]]\n[[Category:Newcastle Falcons (basketball) players]]\n[[Category:UIC Flames men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:American men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Centers (basketball)]]\n\n\n{{US-basketball-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n|name = Ivan Daniels\n|image = \n|caption = \n|league  = \n|team    = \n|position = [center (basketball)Forward]\n|birth_date = Febuary 8th 1963\n|birth_place = Chicago IL, Cook County Hospital.\n|nationality = American & Argentine\n|height_ft = 6  \n|height_in = 10\n|weight_lb = 235\n|number = Grade School #1/High School #53/20/& 41. University #41. Semi Pro Numbers- 9/5/& 15.\n \n|high_school =  Lake Park H.S. Roselle IL.\n|college = [[UIC Flames The University of Illinois at Chicago]] (1981\u20131985)\n| draft_year      = 1985\n| draft_round     = 5\n| draft_pick      = 111\n| draft_team      = [[Indiana Pacers]]\n| draft_league    = NBA\n|career_start = \n|career_end = \n|career_number = \n|years1 = 1985 |team1 = Tonego '65 (basketball) Haaksbergen,Holland\n|years2 = 1986 |team2 = Club Independiente de Z\u00e1rate (basketball) Z\u00e1rate, Argentina\n|years3 = 1987 |team3 = [[Newcastle Falcons (basketball)|Newcastle Falcons]] Newcastle Australia\n|highlights = Captain of the Lancers Frosoph Boys basketball team 1979-80 Leading scorer and rebounder. Second team all conference Upstate 8 1980. Confrences Leading rebounder. MVP Lake Park Thanksgiving Invitational Tournament 1980. All Tournament team at the Luthor North Christmas Tournament 1980. Team Captian Lancers Varsity Boys Basketball Team 1980-81. 1st team All Conference in the Upstate 8, 1981. Inducted into the Lake Park H.S. Athletic Hall of Fame for Basketball. Lake Park High School's all time leading rebounder.\